WEBVTT

00:00.824 --> 00:01.184
Hi there.

00:01.425 --> 00:12.094
Today we're looking at faster neural network training with data echoing by Dummy Choi, Alexander Passo, Christopher J. Shalu and George E. Dahl.

00:12.555 --> 00:22.404
So on a high level, this paper basically says you should repeat data that's already in memory in order to speed up the entire process of neural network training.

00:22.964 --> 00:29.430
And it also says that this can speed up your wall time without hurting your performance too much.

00:29.410 --> 00:32.991
and I have mixed feelings about it.

